---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
		<style>
			body
			main{
				box-sizing: border-box;
				background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.70);
				border-radius: 16px;
				padding: 2rem;
				margin: 1.5rem auto;
			}
			@media (max-width: 480px) {
				h1{
					font-size: 2.3rem;
				}
				main{
					max-width: 350px;
					padding: 1rem;
					margin: 0.5rem auto;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>🖥️ Hello, fellow tech enjoyers!</h1>

			<p>
				Welcome to my personal blog! This is where I share my projects,
				experiments, and thoughts on web development, programming,
				3D printing, self-hosting, Linux, and all things tech.
			</p>

			<p>
				I enjoy building things, learning how they work, and occasionally
				breaking them in the process. Whether it's exploring a new framework,
				designing something to print, automating everyday tasks, or diving
				into open-source software, you'll find my experiences documented here.
			</p>

			<h2>What you'll find here</h2>

			<ul>
				<li>💻 Web development tutorials and experiments</li>
				<li>⚙️ Programming tips, tools, and interesting discoveries</li>
				<li>🖨️ 3D printing projects and design ideas</li>
				<li>🐧 Linux, self-hosting, and homelab adventures</li>
				<li>🛠️ Project write-ups and things I've learned along the way</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Why this blog?</h2>

			<p>
				I wanted a place to document what I'm learning, share solutions to
				problems I've encountered, and hopefully help others who run into
				the same challenges. If even one post saves someone a few hours of
				debugging, it'll have done its job.
			</p>

			<p>
				Thanks for stopping by, and I hope you find something interesting!
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
